<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="20.[820,1459,303,872]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Body deep; greatest depth contained 3.0 to 3.5, caudal peduncle depth 8.1 to 8.9 times in SL; head length 2.5 to 3.0, predorsal distance 2.0, caudal peduncle length 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4605" metricValueMax="1.6764" metricValueMin="1.2446" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="in" value="5.75" valueMax="6.6" valueMin="4.9">4.9 to 6.6 in</quantity>
SL; snout length 2.2 to 2.5, horizontal orbital diameter 2.9 to 3.7 and least interorbital width 
<quantity box="[1329,1459,431,456]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.571999999999999" metricValueMax="4.826" metricValueMin="4.318" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="in" value="1.7999999999999998" valueMax="1.9" valueMin="1.7">1.7 to 1.9 in</quantity>
HL. Mouth terminal; premaxilla and dentary with 3 teeth, no maxillary teeth. Lateral line with 42 or 43 pored scales; transverse series above lateral line with 5½ or 6 scale rows and below with 5 or 5½ scale rows. Dorsal fin with 12, pectoral fin with 16 or 17, pelvic fin with 9, anal fin with 10 and caudal fin with 19 rays (
<bibRefCitation author="Garavello, Britski" box="[1174,1447,623,648]" firstAuthor="Garavello" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="67 - 74" refId="ref80986" refString="Garavello JC, Britski HA. Leporinus macrocephalus sp. n. da bacia do rio Paraguai (Ostariophysi, Anostomidae). Naturalia. 1988; 13: 67 - 74." type="journal article" year="1988">Garavello, Britski, 1988</bibRefCitation>
). Ground color dark-grey; isthmus and abdomen yellowish; scales with dark-brown border, conferring reticulated pattern to body; three dark-brown blotches over lateral line (first vertically enlongated, second and third rounded), more visible in young specimens, inconspicuous or absent in large specimens. Dorsal, anal and caudal fin darker, pectoral and pelvic fins lighter (
<bibRefCitation author="Graca, Pavanelli" box="[1167,1422,847,872]" firstAuthor="Graca" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="58 - 64" refId="ref84115" refString="Pavanelli CS, Graca WJ, Zawadzki CH, Britski HA, Vidotti AP, Avelino GS, Verissimo S. Fishes from the Corumba Reservoir, Paranaiba River drainage, upper rio Parana basin, State of Goias, Brazil. Check List. 2007; 3 (1): 58 - 64." type="journal article" year="2007">Graça, Pavanelli, 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[820,1459,912,968]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[820,1137,912,936]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Maximum standard length.</emphasis>
500.0 mm (
<bibRefCitation author="Graca, Pavanelli" firstAuthor="Graca" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="58 - 64" refId="ref84115" refString="Pavanelli CS, Graca WJ, Zawadzki CH, Britski HA, Vidotti AP, Avelino GS, Verissimo S. Fishes from the Corumba Reservoir, Paranaiba River drainage, upper rio Parana basin, State of Goias, Brazil. Check List. 2007; 3 (1): 58 - 64." type="journal article" year="2007">Graça, Pavanelli, 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[820,1416,1008,1033]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="20.[820,1416,1008,1033]" box="[820,1416,1008,1033]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[820,967,1008,1032]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Distribution.</emphasis>
Río 
<collectingCountry box="[1018,1117,1009,1033]" name="Paraguay" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
and upper rio Paraná basin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[820,1460,1073,1289]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[820,929,1073,1097]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Garavello, Britski" baseAuthorityYear="1988" box="[947,1282,1073,1097]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Megaleporinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrocephalus">
<emphasis box="[947,1282,1073,1097]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Megaleporinus macrocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Garavello, Britski" authorityYear="1988" box="[856,1134,1105,1129]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Leporinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrocephalus">
<emphasis box="[856,1134,1105,1129]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Leporinus macrocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Graca, Pavanelli" box="[1189,1456,1105,1129]" firstAuthor="Graca" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="58 - 64" refId="ref84115" refString="Pavanelli CS, Graca WJ, Zawadzki CH, Britski HA, Vidotti AP, Avelino GS, Verissimo S. Fishes from the Corumba Reservoir, Paranaiba River drainage, upper rio Parana basin, State of Goias, Brazil. Check List. 2007; 3 (1): 58 - 64." type="journal article" year="2007">Graça, Pavanelli (2007)</bibRefCitation>
. Ramirez 
<emphasis box="[912,962,1137,1161]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">et al.</emphasis>
(2016) described the new genus, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ramirez, Birindelli, Galetti Junior" authorityYear="2016" box="[1294,1452,1137,1161]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Megaleporinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1294,1452,1137,1161]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Megaleporinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and proposed the new combination. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Garavello, Britski" baseAuthorityYear="1988" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Megaleporinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrocephalus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Megaleporinus macrocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a non-native species from the upper rio 
<collectingRegion box="[820,891,1233,1257]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Paraná</collectingRegion>
and its occurrence in the region can be associated with fish-farming and escapes from recreational angling ponds.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
